postOrder.name: Post-Order Survey
postOrder.description: Feedback from customers after placing a Dinneroo order

dropoff.name: Dropoff Survey
dropoff.description: Feedback from people who browsed but didn't order
strengths: What people wanted but couldn't find
useFor: Discovering dishes/cuisines people wanted but we don't have

orders.name: Snowflake Orders
limitations: Only what we offer (can't show unmet demand)

ogSurvey.name: OG Survey
ogSurvey.warning: Pre-launch stated preference - validate with behavioral data
useFor: Triangulation only - never as sole source

avgRating.name: Average Rating
avgRating.methodology: Mean of 1-5 star ratings from verified orders
avgRating.calculation: AVG(RATING_STARS) WHERE RATING_STARS IS NOT NULL

totalOrders.name: Total Orders
totalOrders.methodology: Count of all Dinneroo orders in the dataset

surveyResponses.name: Survey Responses
surveyResponses.methodology: Count of completed post-order survey responses

dishesScored.name: Dishes Scored
dishesScored.methodology: Count of dish types in master scoring framework

zonesAnalyzed.name: Zones Analyzed
zonesAnalyzed.methodology: All zones from Anna's ground truth supply data
caveats: 1,105 zones have no order activity yet

mvpZones.name: MVP Zones
mvpZones.methodology: Zones meeting MVP criteria: 5+ partners, 5+ cuisines, 20+ dishes
mvpZones.calculation: COUNT(*) WHERE partners >= 5 AND cuisines >= 5 AND dishes >= 20

avgSalesPerDish.name: Avg Sales Per Dish
avgSalesPerDish.methodology: Average order count per dish type across all zones

deliverooRating.name: Dish Rating
deliverooRating.methodology: Mean rating for orders containing this dish type
caveats: Rating may reflect partner not dish

mealSatisfaction.name: Meal Satisfaction
mealSatisfaction.methodology: % of respondents satisfied or very satisfied with meal

repeatIntent.name: Repeat Intent
repeatIntent.methodology: % of respondents who would order again

dishSuitability.name: Dish Suitability
dishSuitability.methodology: 1-5 scale rating of dish suitability for family meals

openTextRequests.name: Open-Text Requests
openTextRequests.methodology: Count of unprompted mentions in open-text fields

wishlistPct.name: Wishlist %
wishlistPct.methodology: % of respondents who added dish to wishlist

demandStrength.name: Demand Strength
demandStrength.methodology: Composite score based on order volume and growth
demandStrength.calculation: Normalized score combining order count and trend

consumerPreference.name: Consumer Preference
consumerPreference.methodology: Composite score from satisfaction and intent metrics
consumerPreference.calculation: Weighted average of satisfaction and repeat intent

coverageGap.name: Coverage Gap
coverageGap.methodology: % of zones where dish is not available

zonePartners.name: Zone Partners
zonePartners.methodology: Count of unique partners in zone

zoneCuisines.name: Zone Cuisines
zoneCuisines.methodology: Count of unique cuisine types in zone

zoneRating.name: Zone Rating
zoneRating.methodology: Average rating for orders in zone
caveats: May be skewed by few partners

cuisineSupplyGap.name: Cuisine Supply Gap
cuisineSupplyGap.methodology: Zones where cuisine supply is below average

cuisineQualityGap.name: Cuisine Quality Gap
cuisineQualityGap.methodology: Cuisines where rating is below benchmark (4.0)
caveats: May be affected by partner mix

satisfaction.name: Satisfaction Rate
satisfaction.definition: % of respondents who are 'Very Satisfied' OR 'Satisfied'

strongAdvocate.name: Strong Advocate
strongAdvocate.definition: Customers meeting ALL THREE: Loved it + Very Satisfied + Would reorder

frequencyCategory.name: Customer Frequency
frequencyCategory.definition: Based on days since last order

selectionGaps.evidence: 63% families eat regularly (OG Survey n=404), 0 supply, 5 open-text requests
selectionGaps.impact: Missing high-demand dish - #11 most eaten by families

selectionGaps.evidence: 60% eat regularly, only Las Iguanas, 31 open-text requests
78% eat regularly - 2nd highest after burgers, ~0% supply
selectionGaps.impact: Highest latent demand - families don't expect on delivery

selectionGaps.evidence: 68% eat regularly, 0.07% of orders, 34 open-text requests
49% eat regularly, highest suitability score (4.4), 75-89% scratch cook
selectionGaps.impact: High effort dish families would outsource

selectionGaps.evidence: 70% eat regularly - highest consumption, 17 open-text requests

ogSurveyComparison.biasWarning: Pre-launch stated preference - validate with behavioral data

normalizationMetadata.explanation: Sales metrics are normalized for supply differences to ensure fair comparison across dishes with different availability.
normalizationMetadata.formula: Normalized Sales = Total Orders / (Zones Available × Days Listed)
normalizationMetadata.example: A dish in 10 zones with 1000 orders scores the same as a dish in 100 zones with 10,000 orders

metricsNotNormalized.name: Deliveroo Rating
metricsNotNormalized.reason: Per-order average, not affected by zone count

principles.name: Triangulated Scoring
principles.detail: Combines behavioral (orders, ratings) with survey (satisfaction, intent) and qualitative (open-text) data

principles.name: Behavioral Validation
principles.description: OG Survey claims checked against actual orders
principles.detail: Stated preference from pre-launch survey is validated with revealed preference from Snowflake

principles.name: Supply Normalization
principles.detail: Prevents dishes in more zones from unfairly outranking limited-availability dishes

principles.name: Gap Analysis
principles.description: Coverage gaps prioritized by demand evidence
principles.detail: High coverage gap alone doesn't mean opportunity - must have demand signal

principles.name: Family Signals
principles.description: Kids Full & Happy (7.5%), Fussy Eater Friendly (5.5%)
principles.detail: Family-specific metrics weighted into scoring to reflect Dinneroo's target audience
